hey i'm having a weird issue with my shopify theme. on mobile the product image is overlapping the title text like it's just sitting right on top of it. i tried changing the margin but it didn't do anything. here is my css snippet for the product header:

.product-header {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  padding: 20px;
}

.product-image {
  width: 100%;
  height: auto;
}

.product-title {
  font-size: 24px;
  margin-top: 10px;
}

any idea why it's overlapping on small screens?

Ah, it sounds like a classic case of the 'Giant Goblin' problem, where the product image is too big for the title text on mobile devices. You might want to consider adding a responsive design feature to your CSS, like using media queries to adjust the styles on smaller screens. For example, you could try adding something like this:

@media (max-width: 600px) {
  .product-image {
    max-width: 100%;
  }
  .product-title {
    font-size: 18px;
  }
}

This should help your product image and title text to coexist peacefully on smaller screens. Remember, when it comes to CSS, it's all about finding the right balance, just like a well-balanced goblin. Happy coding!
